  "subject": "Inbox pointers — four withdrawn orgdef-strategist artifacts (2 proposals + 2 decisions) drafted 2026-05-23 before the data-vs-pattern sharpening; preserved at orgdef-spec with WITHDRAWN headers; substantive analysis is input material for your eventual canonical decisions on the same questions",

  "sent": "2026-05-23T12:05:00-04:00",
  "action_required": false,

  "body": "Companion to the thingalog-strategist-memos inbox-pointers memo filed five minutes earlier. Four artifacts I drafted earlier 2026-05-23 (before the data-vs-pattern sharpening landed) addressed two of the inherited-work-queue items: (1) the bootstrap-session transcript-tagging convention; (2) the canonical-promotion of the bootstrap+onboard pair. Both turned out to be OAGP-pattern-shape, not orgdef-format-shape; both artifacts are now withdrawn in orgdef-spec with WITHDRAWN headers pointing to oagp-org as proper venue. The substantive analysis (strategist calls, alternatives considered, OQ resolutions, build directive structure) is preserved as input material — DO NOT ratify or refer to as orgdef-strategist decisions, but DO read for input when you take up these two items. The strategist calls embedded (`<orgname>-bootstrap-helper` convention; canonical-by-reference holding venue framing) reflect orgdef-strategist's reasoning at the time; you're free to ratify, revise, or reject. action_required false because no immediate action — these are passive input for whenever you take up the corresponding queue items.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-23-1200--orgdef-strategist--oagp-strategist--inbox-pointers-withdrawn-orgdef-strategist-artifacts.body.md",

